text:
North Hempstead Turnpike, north side, between Main Street (left) and 140th Street (right), showing an old house occupied by the following. A. Remsen, 1860; J. Clark, 1873 to 1896; H. Elliot, 1891; and also one John Sharkey. Eugene Armbruster states these views of the house show it at its new location. However, the Queens Atlas of 1891 shows the house at the N.E. corner of Remsen Ave. (Jaggar Street and Ireland Mill Road, now North Hempstead Turnpike). This is a set of three views from slightly different angles.

January 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

text:
North Hempstead Turnpike, at S.E. corner of Main Street, showing an old home and a new real estate development. This property was owned by J. Clark in 1891 and 1909. It was part of a 63-acre farm lying on both sides of the Turnpike.

P. L. Sperr
April 19, 1936
